<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Firewall spell says "duration" where maybe it should say "range" or something. Firewall has no "duration", and the name is misleading as it doesn't have any "wall" characteristics - it's effect looks like a line. <p>
I'm suspecting the spell's code used to be a durable effect like noxious cloud but the description wasn't updated. 
</p>
<p>
Either the spell's code or its description is wrong. 
</p>
<p>
(I haven't checked the 2.3.0 version wand, but if I recall correctly it has the bug too) 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a></strong>: Actually, the effects last for the duration of the spell. If a monster walks thru where you shot the beam while the spell is still active, they will take damage... At least that's how it should work. So, if you shot it down a hallway, the monsters coming a few turns after you used the spell will also take the damage because the firewall is still there. 
</p>
<p>
Simon: Couldn't replicate this effect after a few tries. How do you do that? 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a></strong>: Well, I said that's how it should work. I never tried myself, but you can find the function on spells2.c I think. It certainly takes a time variable for it to work, if it works. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./ZasVid">ZasVid</a></strong>: Last time I used Firewall, it WAS doing what <a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a> described (with ToME 226, I think). 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: This is not a bug, the spell effects last for the given duration (checked in ToME 2.3.0). Using text mode even shows a shimmering effect that lasts for the duration of the spell. 
</p>
<p>
There are two problems left: 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 The spell / effect name could be chosen better (it's not a wall, but a persistent beam) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 The shimmering effect should also be visible in graphic modi, but this is already on the bug list: 
</p>
</li>

    </ul><pre>[B]- Make persistent effects visible when using graphics
</pre></div><div id="footer">


